{
  "texts": [
    "[18-19] The 49th Statistical Report on Internet Development in China, released by the China Internet Network Information Center (CNNIC), reveals that around three-quarters of internet users in China use the internet to look up health-related information, with 84.5% of those in need of health advice turning to online sources.",
    "This trend is particularly noticeable in the area of adolescent growth and development, where both patients and their parents often rely on internet resources.",
    "With the rising prominence of Large Language Models (LLMs), there is an anticipation that more patients and parents will start using LLM chatbots to seek information on adolescent growth and development.",
    "Nonetheless, the reliability of the answers provided by LLM-Chatbots to these frequent questions about adolescent health is yet to be determined.",
    "[20] Unlike earlier healthcare chatbots that relied on extracting information from tailored datasets, LLMs such as ChatGPT are trained using self-supervised learning on diverse internet content."
  ]
}